    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1927"/>, pp. <citedRange>156-157</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#ferri1932"/>, p. <citedRange>274</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1933"/>, pp. <citedRange>113-115</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.100</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>019000</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2014"/>, n. <citedRange>1</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>64.2012</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" quantity="4" precision="low" unit="character"/></name> <persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-63777"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Εὐαγγελίδας"><supplied reason="lost">Ε</supplied>ὐαγγελίδα</name></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπό</supplied>λλω<supplied reason="lost">νι</supplied></name></persName> 
                        <w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w>. 
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested"><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" precision="low" unit="character"/><orig>η</orig><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="1"/><gap reason="lost" atLeast="4" atMost="5" unit="character"/><name nymRef="#_ς"><seg part="F">ς</seg></name></persName> <g type="punct">:</g> <w lemma="ἐργάζομαι">ἠργάσσατο</w>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem resp="#oliverio1927"><supplied reason="lost">Ε</supplied>ὐαγγελίδα</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1933"><supplied reason="lost">ἐπ᾿ Ἐ</supplied>υαγγελίδα</rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <app loc="3">
                        <lem><gap reason="lost" quantity="6" precision="low" unit="character"/><orig>η</orig><gap reason="illegible" unit="character" quantity="1"/>
                                    <gap reason="lost" atLeast="4" atMost="5" unit="character"/>ς</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1927"><supplied reason="lost">Δ</supplied>η<unclear>μ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ήτριο</supplied>ς</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#ferri1932"><supplied reason="lost">Λ</supplied>ήμ<supplied reason="lost">νιο</supplied>ς</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1933"><supplied reason="lost">Τ</supplied>ηλ<supplied reason="lost">οκλῆ</supplied>ς</rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Un tel fils</supplied>d'Euangelidas <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré</supplied> à Apollon comme dîme. 
                        <supplied reason="lost">Un tel</supplied> a exécuté.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So and so son</supplied> of Euangelidas <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> to Apollo as a tithe. 
                        Made by <supplied reason="lost">so and so</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale figlio</supplied> di Euangelidas <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato</supplied> ad Apollo come decima. 
                        <supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> fece.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
               <p>Oliverio dated the lettering in the fifth century, which seems too high.</p>
                <p>As only eta and an ambiguous letter (lambda or mu) are preserved at left of l. 3, it seems wise to restrain from restoring the sculptor's name,
                    a fortiori to guess that it might be the Lemnian Alcamenes (a guess of <bibl><ptr target="#ferri1932"/></bibl>, rejected by all commentators).</p>
        	      <p><bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2014"/></bibl>, having not found the stone, cautiously expressed some doubts about the readings.</p>
            </div></body>
